beer.beer_description: Dębowe is a full light lager - a bottom-fermentated beer. Its richer taste and higher extract content make it stand out among other lagers. Because of its sophisticated taste, it is best served at 10 degrees Celsius, a slightly higher temperature than for a regular lager. It derives its special character from carefully selected ingredients and a proper brewing process. 14.2°Blg
